Author: Jincor
Title: [ANN][ICO is LIVE!] Jincor - Blockchain-powered enterprise communications
Body: Hello!  Etherparty offers only smart contract constructor - Jincor's functionality extends far beyond creation of smart contracts.  Jibrel offers financial instruments for businesses - we will implement such instruments based on smart contracts also.  So in general our idea is put all the tools which businesses needed in terms of blockchain economy in one place - our platform. An on top of Etherparty/Jibrel functions we'll implement a companies verification, decentralised arbitration system and a messaging.  Moreover both projects above works on Ethereum blockchain. Jincor is based on a own private blockchain, which is definitely much superior and scalable for enterprise application. Jincor blockchain infrastructure based on Hyperledger framework is ready and implemented in a wallets module in our beta https://beta.jincor.com (Soon we'll connect smart contract constructor module to beta also).  I recommend you to read our technical paper if you want to know more about how our system will work from inside: https://jincor.com/technical-paper

Author: Jincor
Title: [ANN][ICO is LIVE!] Jincor - Blockchain-powered enterprise communications
Body: Jincor ICO will start on the 1st of December 2017.  Setting up one of the most transparent ICOs up to date and making sure that contributors funds are used to build up Jincor as scheduled in our roadmap, has required us to add much more resources to our legal team and rebuild the future company’s legal structure. Along with our partners, we were over-optimistic about an appropriate timeframe and we take all the criticism. However, there’s always a risk of that happening in case you are building something exceptional, a product that is supposed to revolutionize the industry, inevitably changing the way how modern business operates. We are doing our best to make it happen and appreciate your being onboard with us.

Author: Jincor
Title: [ANN][ICO is LIVE!] Jincor - Blockchain-powered enterprise communications
Body: Hello friends,  We have very important news!  Our ICO campaign will start on November 15 — two weeks later than it’s been planned before.  Although everything is now ready for the campaign start, we’re willingly taking responsibility for all the risks associated with this decision, as we aim to run one of the most legally transparent ICOs that have ever happened in the industry.  Our legal consultant is tier 1 international law firm, one of the most trusted law firms in the world. It helps us to make our ICO available to U.S. investors, and the full compliance with KYC / AML (Know Your Client / Anti-Money Laundering) requirements has taken us longer than we could foresee.  And since honesty and transparency have always been integral parts of Jincor brand, we’ve decided to move the date of the ICO campaign start.  However, the additional time we get will not be spent on this “paper-handling” work only — it will let us release a product, which will reveal the platform potential in more entirety, as well as provide more secure and convenient environment for participating in our ICO (for instance, it will give us even more time to test the isolation and protection system for Jincor infrastructure, which we are working on along with ITSumma).  Therefore, we believe that in the long-term perspective it’s the most proper decision, which has been made in the interests of our clients and the community supporting the project. So, we hope for your understanding and look forward to seeing you at Jincor ICO on November 15!  P.S. All the documents, including Whitepaper and Business Summary, as well as our website have been updated in accordance with the new ICO start date. You can read them one more time on jincor.com.

Author: itsjohnny
Title: [ANN][ICO is LIVE!] Jincor - Blockchain-powered enterprise communications
Body: https://i.imgur.com/QgJx8Bw.png  Jincor roadshow now goes to Monaco, and today we are participating in Monaco Growth Forums Blockchain Summit. (https://monacogrowthforums.com/)  It’s an event where the world’s most groundbreaking companies and international investors meet. Author: Jincor
Title: [ANN][ICO is LIVE!] Jincor - Blockchain-powered enterprise communications
Body: Hello!  We have reached our maximum goal for this stage and collected altogether 1207 ETH.   We are happy to announce that a new adviser - Marcus Killick - joined our team. Running an ICO and building business after it often might be a tricky thing due to lack of clear rules and regulations about it. Marcus - is a top notch lawyer expert on those matters, as he is an acting CEO of ISOLAS LLP Gibraltar law firm. Apart of that Marcus is the Non Executive Chairman of the Gibraltar Stock Exchange (GSX) and a non executive director of a number of other companies including the Gibraltar International Bank as well as a  Chairperson of the Commission of the Office of Fair Trading. Marcus was one of the founding directors of the United Kingdom Association of Compliance Officers (Subsequently renamed the Compliance Institute). And was even awarded the OBE (British Queen's honour given to an individual for a major local role in any activity such as business, charity or the public sector) in the 2014 New Years Honours List. Marcus will be our Jurisdiction advisor and we look forward working with him as a team!

Author: Jincor
Title: [ANN][ICO is LIVE!] Jincor - Blockchain-powered enterprise communications
Body: Hello, friends!  Project Jincor, blockchain ecosystem for enterprise interactions, became an honored sponsor of cryptocurrency event Coinference, which will be held in Moscow on the 30 of July.  During the conference experts in the blockchain sphere will present the review of successful and failed ICO companies, share the analytical data of trading instruments and mining infrastructure, discuss aspects of cryptocurrency regulation in different countries.  As a special event in the frame of the conference Vagan Abelyan, co-founder of Jincor project, will make a presentation of his blockchain-platform and share the legal knowledge on cryptocurrency issues, accumulated by the Jincor judicial team, unveil data about enterprises that already use cryptocurrencies in financial routine and estimations  of entrepreneurs on the perspectives of the area. Vagan will also review the changes in cryptocurrency and ICO regulation in the legal system of USA. Life broadcast of the upcoming event will be available on forklog.com  The event will take place on Nizhny Susalny alley, building 5, block 4 (Moscow, Russia).  Event description (on Russian): http://coinference.info/

Author: Jincor
Title: [ANN][ICO is LIVE!] Jincor - Blockchain-powered enterprise communications
Body: Unlike Slack, we are focused on developing an ecosystem for the corporate segment (B2B). Slack is the user's messenger.  The idea of our project is that all the elements for corporate interaction within the framework of the blockchain economy are in one product and work as a unified system. The messenger is just one of the platform modules. You can find out more about the structure of the platform by reading our WP: https://s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/jincor-ico/whitepaper.pdf

Author: Jincor
Title: [ANN][ICO is LIVE!] Jincor - Blockchain-powered enterprise communications
Body: Cheers! To put it simple, whether we raise $5-10M or not, our milestones and long-term strategy won't be changed or canceled, since the amount of resources may only affect our development and growth dynamics. It might just take us a bit longer than expected, but anyway our team will reach its goals and everything will work out in best interests of our investors. With that being said, we are quite sure that the community will support us and we find the scenario that you have outlined highly improbable. As for your question, the tentative date for an ICO start is November 1st, so follow us and don't miss the official announcement!
